{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionBioinformatics synthesizes computer programming, biology, and big data to aid scientists in perceiving and detecting paradigms in biological and medical information [1][2][3].",
    "It is significantly suitable for studying DNA sequencing, as it allows scientists to arrange a great deal of data [4,5].",
    "The area of computer science, namely bioinformatics, is applied to evaluate whole-genome sequencing information [6,7].",
    "This contains software improvement, algorithm, analysis, pipeline, transferring, and storage/database improvement of genomics information.",
    "In other words, bioinformatics is described as applying analysis and computation tools to receive and interpret biological data [8,9]."
  ]
}